```

# 🚀 APIs in System Design

In modern architectures almost everything communicates through APIs.

```text
Mobile App
      ↓
API Gateway
      ↓
User Service
Order Service
Payment Service
Notification Service
      ↓
Database
```

This allows:

* Independent development
* Scalability
* Reusability
* Easier maintenance

Without APIs, microservices would not exist.

# 🏁 Final Takeaway

An API is the communication layer that allows different software systems to interact safely and predictably.

Modern applications are essentially collections of APIs working together behind a user interface. Whether it's Uber, Netflix, Instagram, Amazon, or ChatGPT, APIs are the backbone that connects frontend applications, backend services, databases, and third-party systems.


